step2"><label>Apply the open triangular bandage to the front of his chest with apex towards injured arm</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Place upper end of bandage over the sound shoulder and let other end hang down toward the ground</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>Carry upper end rounf the back of neck and forward over shoulder of the injusred site</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Carry upper end round the back of neck and forward over soulder of injured side</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Bend injured arm carefully and elbow and place forearm across chest , with hand pointing to opposite shoulder</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Bring up the lower end of bandage over the forearm and tie to the uppwer end in front of shoulder on injured site just below on collar bone</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step8"><label>Fold apex forward over elbow and fix with safety pin</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step9"><label>The Small Arm Sling -Use a broad fold bandage 
-Stand in front of patient and lay one end of bandage over sound shoulder 
-Bring it round the back of neck and forwards over the shoulder of injured side
-Bend elbow , of injured arm carefully placing the wrist and hand in bandage so that they are little higher thean elbow
-Bring up the lower end of bandage and tie with upper end just below collar bone on injured side 


Improvised sling 

-Placing injured arm inside the buttoned up coat or waist coat
-Pinning the sleeve cuff of the injured arm to lapel of the caot on uninjured side
-Turning up the bottom edge of the coat on the injured side and pinning it to opposite lapel
-Using belts , braces , neckties or tapes</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>